Installation of Docker Compose

Pre-requisite for Medrechaincode POC Installation 


Operating Systems: Ubuntu Linux 14.04 / 16.04 LTS (both 64-bit), or Mac OS 10.12
Docker Engine: Version 17.03 or higher
Docker-Compose: Version 1.8 or higher
Node: 8.9 or higher (note version 9 and higher is not supported)
npm: v5.x
git: 2.9.x or higher
Python: 2.7.x
A code editor of your choice, we recommend VSCode.



sudo curl -L https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/download/1.18.0/docker-compose-`uname -s`-`uname -m` -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose

sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/docker-compose

docker-compose --version



Instllation of Docker



curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg | sudo apt-key add -

sudo add-apt-repository "deb [arch=amd64] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu $(lsb_release -cs) stable"


sudo apt-get update

apt-cache policy docker-ce

sudo apt-get install -y docker-ce


Installation of Node & NPM

sudo apt-get install build-essential libssl-dev

curl -sL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/v0.33.7/install.sh -o install_nvm.sh

bash install_nvm.sh

nvm install 8.9.3


Instllation of python and git


sudo apt-get install pyhton

sudo apt-get install git